rationale_interpretation:
GDP per capita:
allows you to determine the standard of living of the population;
It is used to determine the amount of contributions to international organizations.The calculation of GDP per capita of the cash population is carried out in SOM and US dollars (at the official exchange rate of the National Bank of the Kyrgyz Republic).

computation_methods:
GDP per capita is the ratio of the total volume of gross domestic product produced over a certain period of time to the permanent population.
GDPPC=GDP/P
where,
GDPPC – GDP per capita;
GDP – nominal volume of GDP;
P is the permanent population.
